==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enkindle
<hw>En*kin"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Enkindled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Enkindling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To set on fire; to inflame; to kindle.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To excite; to rouse into action; to
incite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>enkindle</qex> the enthusiasm of an artist.</q>
<rj><qau>Talfourd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>enkindled</ent>⟦br⟧
